# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

An Actor-RTC echo app that discovers a remote EchoService and sends an echo RPC.

## Quick start

```bash
# 1. Download the remote EchoService proto from the registry
actr install

# 2. Generate Actor framework code from the proto
actr gen -l rust

# 3. Run the app (connects, echoes "hello", prints the reply, and exits)
cargo run
```

## How it works

- `actr.toml` declares a dependency on `echo-echo-server` (the remote EchoService).
- `actr install` fetches `protos/remote/echo-echo-server/echo.proto`.
- `actr gen -l rust` generates `src/generated/` with protobuf types and Actor framework code.
- `src/main.rs` discovers the remote EchoService and sends a single RPC call.

